The paper proposes a framework for automated welding of tubular joints using RGB-D sensors for object detection and a Bi-directional Transition based Rapidly exploring Random Tree (BiTRRT) algorithm for motion planning. This involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for object detection, machine learning (cs.LG) for the BiTRRT algorithm, and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY) for the overall framework.
